<br>
The darkness swirled about Tanj once more and suddenly cold was biting at his bones. His heavy cloak provided some protection from the bite of the frost around him. Slowly Tanj blinked and when his eyes reopened they were greeted by a brilliant white, so stunningly pure and shiny that it dazzled his sight for a few short minutes. His sleeping roll was still encasing his body and making him feel claustrophobic. The large Vah Shir had spent another night in his acrylia studded armor, making it that much easier to move quickly if something should strike in the night. He was confused and couldn’t remember where he was. Something was odd… time had passed, he could feel it. A LOT of time had passed…. He was older. A soft rumble of a half made snore came from off to his side, past the remains of a fire and two spits with the remains of a few snow rabbits. Tanj wriggled his way out of his sleeping roll and stood, rolling it up and placing it back in his pack he hefted his spear and headed over to the other bedroll.<br>
<br>
Grindell was still sleeping, the monk was average size for a human, which meant he was just tall enough to reach Tanj’s shoulders. He nudged the monks bedroll with a booted foot and woke him up. Grindell blinked and let loose a soft chuckle.<br>
<br>
“Up early today eh Tanj?”<br>
<br>
“Lets get going Grindell, we came to hunt lets do it.”<br>
<br>
“Yes I know… I cam to hunt Tanj, you’re just along to provide me with the powers I need to show my superiority to the rest of the world.”<br>
<br>
Tanj held back a smile. Grindell was quite full of himself to the casual listener. The monk was an odd companion that Tanj had befriended a while ago. The two were a very odd pair, deadly in combat and constantly insulting each other. To anyone not used to hearing their banter it sounded as if they hated each other, in fact they had some sort of friendship however tenuous. Grindell was up as Tanj sat down to focus his mind on gathering the necessary spirits for the days hunt. The monk finished rolling up his sleeping pad and placed it in his pack. He traveled light, much lighter than Tanj, and the cold didn’t seem to bother him at all though Tanj could feel himself shivering occasionally under his fur.<br>
<br>
“Today the Frost Giants are going to get a taste of my fists.”<br>
<br>
Tanj couldn’t resist the insult he instantly thought up and replied quickly.<br>
<br>
“What are you going to do? Break their ankles? You are probably the size of their big toes.”<br>
<br>
Grindell smirked.<br>
<br>
“Laugh it up fuzz butt, all you do is sit in the snow and watch… like some sadistic voyeur who likes watching things die.”<br>
<br>
Tanj nodded, smiling.<br>
<br>
“Perhaps, perhaps not.”<br>
<br>
Grindell didn’t respond, so Tanj went back to his meditations. The monk and he had left the Coldain city of Thurgadin over a day ago and even with the blessing of the wolf the deep snows had forced them to take their time. They had been to the Eastern Wastes before, but that was over a month ago. Things had gone well, they had slain several giants. After a few months doing other things they had met back up in Thurg and decided to go hunting once more. The partnership felt a bit more meaningful than a full hunting party. And besides, the stories were much better, two adventurers fighting against the towering giants of the Kromzek. Tanj felt the final spirit he required agree to aid him, and he reflexively closed his open palms, feeling their power come into him for his use. He stood up and grabbed his spear, Grindell was finishing his daily exercises, warming up muscles for fighting the bright clear day would bring. His fists punched the air so fast they blurred, Tanj didn’t think the giants stood a chance.<br>
<br>
“Well then lets get started shall we, we should return with a few heads to give to the Coldain to strengthen them as allies.”<br>
<br>
“Yea lets get to it, can’t wait to kick some giant butt.”<br>
<br>
Tanj nodded and began to cast a multitude of spells, watching Grindell’s physique stretch slightly as his strength increased by a respectable amount. After a few minutes of binding the spirits to Grindell’s person he bound himself to a few spirits as well for protection. Grindell punched the air experimentally and seemed satisfied with the result as his hands moving in slicing motions with a wind loud enough to sound like he was actually cutting the crisp air. Tanj went back to meditating and gathered a few more spirits, offensive ones that would aid him in times of battle. The spirit of torment, and agony came to him quickly as always, eager to do their part by burning his enemies with swift poison or the slower acting disease. He stood once more this time ready for battle. He motioned to Grindell.<br>
<br>
“You’re the monk, it is your show.”<br>
<br>
“Right then lets get going.”<br>
<br>
Grindell took off with a speed possessed by no normal human, but Tanj kept up easily the wolf spirit in them both allowing them to move swifter than normal. The day passed quickly at first, hunting down and killing whatever crossed their pathes while slowly making their way to the ominous wall in the distance. A huge granite structure that marked the domain of Kael Drakkel, the wall was a marker that they were heading into Frost Giant territory. They crossed paths with a few scouts of the Frost Giant empire, all easily dispatched before they could call for help. Before midday struck they were at the single opening in the huge wall, the gate that lead to the giant courtyard that would eventually take them into the caves of Kael. Hovering his above the chasm that was guarded by the two giants they decided what to do next.<br>
<br>
“So how about it spiritcaller? We going to do this and take it to these guys? Or hang back and keep beating on the scouts?”<br>
<br>
“Lets bring back some new trophies… the scouts pose no threat anymore. Try to split them first, I’d rather not deal with two at a time especially not these guards.”<br>
<br>
Grindell nodded grinning like Tanj was explaining to a cleric how to pray to their god.<br>
<br>
“I know what I’m doing Tanj.”<br>
<br>
A quick decision of will and the hovering spell was removed, Grindell dropped, and right behind him came Tanj, they fell a good distance before landing into the snow. Grindell rolled easily to get back on his feet and quickly recover from the shock of landing, his training in such things helping his natural reflexes. Tanj’s reflexes were honed better but he had no training like the human, and his recover was a bit more awkward.<br>
<br>
“Here comes one now…”<br>
<br>
Grindell didn’t finish but ran off and proceeded to yell at the top of his lungs at the nearest giant. Insulting his mother most likely, it was his usual pulling strategy and it still made Tanj want to laugh.<br>
<br>
“Look out I got one on my butt.”<br>
<br>
Tanj blinked and shrugged.<br>
<br>
“What you want me to help you out? I thought Mr. Big Shot could take a little giant on his own.”<br>
<br>
“VERY funny guess you get to deal with him on your own!”<br>
<br>
Grindell laughed then gasped as if his heart had stopped, then fell face first into the snow not even flinching as he hit the freezing cold ground. Tanj gaped, then realized that the monk had probably intentionally stopped his heart…. Feigning death, the giant in the distance was approaching rapidly and he didn’t look happy. Tanj laughed not thinking Grindell would actually be serious. Several more huge steps by the large armored beast and Tanj was ready to take the monk seriously.<br>
<br>
“Ok ok I was kidding!”<br>
<br>
Grindell popped back up to his feet in a quick motion and grinned.<br>
<br>
“Thought so.”<br>
<br>
The giant approached and Tanj quickly sent off the spirits under his control to annoy and harm the giant so Grindell could dispatch it easily. The monks hands moved swiftly making quick work of the giant despite his smaller size. With a resounding *THUD!* the giant’s corpse settled into the snow.<br>
<br>
“Well that wasn’t so hard was it lets do it ag….”<br>
<br>
Grindell’s words were cut off by a horn. Something was coming… That horn meant something that tickled Tanj’s mind but he couldn’t remember what it was. Grindell looked up and behind Tanj towards the chasm and uttered a slurred sentence of expletives that would turn even an Ogre’s face red. Tanj knew that this wasn’t a joke but something serious. He turned to look…. His mind registered what he saw as fast as the quick tongued Grindell said it.<br>
<br>
“Hunting Party… coming our way NOW a GIANT hunting party!”<br>
<br>
Tanj started heading for Kael… he had been there before and knew more than a few hiding spots in the caverns, even the giants didn’t know all the passageways and hiding locations in their city, especially the ones that would fit a race less than half their size.<br>
<br>
“RUN NOW! Head for Kael lets MOVE Grindell!”<br>
<br>
Grindell nodded and started running with Tanj, they passed the gate, the second guard noticing them and running now behind them. It was a huge train of giants, and the hunting party behind them know knew something was amiss as they passed the corpse of their fallen companion. The next series of events happened faster than Tanj could react. Somehow the giants huge steps had caught up with him and Grindell despite the spirit blessing them with speed. Grindell stopped and turned.<br>
<br>
“Keep going!”<br>
<br>
Tanj stopped as well.<br>
<br>
“ARE YOU CRAZY?!”<br>
<br>
“MOVE DAMMIT I’m a monk remember?! I’ll keep them busy for a while and then fall. They’ll think they’ve slain me and it will buy you time to get away.”<br>
<br>
Those precious seconds for that exchange to occur made it worthless. The Giants could see them both clearly now, one bellowed.<br>
<br>
“DAR’KHURA YOU SHALL FINALLY PAY FOR YOUR TRESPASSING ON OUR HOMELANDS!”<br>
<br>
Tanj winced… he was hated more than a little by most of the Giants, and they would likely ignore Grindell to get after him… Tanj turned and continued running for Kael leaving Grindell behind knowing he could fend for himself. He began to hear the pounding of footsteps behind him and felt the sense of urgency rising, he sent out a call to a spirit he rarely used. That of the cheetah. The spirit came to him and he was thankful, but the steps behind him grew and before he could bless himself with the speed of the lanky plains hunter he felt a large book the size of his chest connect with his back. Tanj went flying with a loud grunt, the giant easily punting him quite far. He landed heavily and his teeth gnashed, cutting his cheek. His back ached but he struggled to his feet and cast a spell, the cheetah spirit swelled within him and he ran with a speed so fast even the giants couldn’t keep up. He didn’t stop till he reached the caves of Kael and hid inside. Those hunting him passed by certain they would find him somewhere within the caves. Tanj waited breathing heavily and slowly healing himself and mending his wounds while he waited. After a few minutes he felt it was safe to return and make sure Grindell had made it.<br>
<br>
Tanj ran back out into the huge expanse of snowy white that formed the huge courtyard between the wall and Kael. Grindell was easy to find… he had two large forms looming over him. Tanj approached and found the monk fighting for his life.<br>
<br>
“I told you to get the hell out of here Tanj, get moving now!”<br>
<br>
Grindell managed to shout this at Tanj’s approaching form as he was pummeled by huge fists, he dodged some of the strikes and struck back but it was clear he didn’t stand a chance.<br>
<br>
“Not a chance!”<br>
<br>
Grindell grunted as one huge fist caught him from a blindside it sent him sailing, Tanj had already begun casting a spell to heal his friend, but by the time Grindell’s beaten body had hit the soft snow it was too late. Tanj’s spell didn’t take hold, he could feel Grindell’s spirit leaving his body. The two giants breathed heavily for a few seconds regarding the new comer, Tanj stood there, feeling rage boil up inside of him. Grindell was a friend, one of few Tanj considered true friends. These creatures before him had killed his friend, and the rage that filled him was such that he wanted revenge at any cost. The spirits flew from him sharing his rage and struck the giants with dangerous accuracy.<br>
<br>
“Now its YOUR TURN TO MEET YOUR DOOM!”<br>
<br>
Tanj one of the giants fell swiftly clawing at his body trying to remove the burning sensation he felt in his very blood. The other shrugged off the spirits as if they were nothing, and closed the short distance between him and the shaman. Tanj was in the middle of casting as the fist approached him from directly ahead, but he couldn’t move or the spell would not be complete. The huge knuckles connected and he could feel his ribs creak has he staggered back coughing up blood. But the spell completed itself and his foe now found himself moving so slowly that it was nearly laughable. Tanj got to his feet and spit blood, then rooted the giant to the ground with another spell before backing off a safe distance he yelled at the giant before him.<br>
<br>
“NOT SO TOUGH NOW ARE YOU! Try fighting someone ONE ON ONE!”<br>
<br>
He sent spirit after vengeful spirit at the giant who had yet to respond to his anger, most of which bounced off the beast with little effect. A few held and slowly began to eat at the soul of the huge creature. Eventually his reserve was spent, the spirits had all left him. Tanj knew this was going to be a close match…. The giant was dying slowly but the spirits were fleeting now, and the giant would be free of his bonds any moment. Tanj cast one more spell hoping it took hold it did, but in doing so the bond broke free. The giant was coming, and all Tanj could do was run and hope the giant died before it reached him. He was tired and with no spirit to heal him he was close to unconsciousness, the giant behind him was flagging badly as well, but was not willing to give up the fight either. Then the turning point occurred… Tanj had circled back around without realizing it, and his foot caught something causing him to trip. Grindell’s corpse lay just behind him as he struggled back to his feet. The monks body had slowly began to sink into the deep snow. Tanj had time to get fully to his feet and take another step when the final blow struck him from behind blackening his vision, he was unconscious and near death before he hit the ground.<br>
<br>
Hours later his vision slowly cleared to the sight of a cleric standing over him. Grindell stood next to the High Elf woman, wrapped in many thick bandages. Tanj stuttered.<br>
<br>
“How…?”<br>
<br>
Grindell smiled.<br>
<br>
“You know me, I’m just a big faker… but that time wasn’t so much on purpose. I didn’t manage to regain consciousness till you were out cold but I beat that bastard down for you. Yer tough furbutt I’ll give you that.”<br>
<br>
Grindell motioned to a large pile of armor behind him, looted from the giant Tanj had fought. The vah shir tried to laugh but the pain it brought him simply knocked him out once more, this time the blackness remained.<br>
<br>
He began to fall for a third time, this time Grindell’s voice echoed at him from the darkness.<br>
<br>
